Version 0.3; mark unmaintained.

commit.message: Upgrade pytest for Python 3.5 compat; drop 2.6 and Django 1.6.
Drop support for Python 3.2 (and PyPy3), since pip/Travis no longer support.

Merge pull request #22 from adamchainz/readthedocs.io

Convert readthedocs links for their .org -> .io migration for hosted projects

Convert readthedocs links for their .org -> .io migration for hosted projects

As per [their blog post of the 27th April](https://blog.readthedocs.com/securing-subdomains/) ‘Securing subdomains’:

> Starting today, Read the Docs will start hosting projects from subdomains on the domain readthedocs.io, instead of on readthedocs.org. This change addresses some security concerns around site cookies while hosting user generated data on the same domain as our dashboard.

Test Plan: Manually visited all the links I’ve modified.
Complete the removal of django-trunk envs from .travis.yml.
No need to test on later Django versions than 1.8.
Document that support ends with Django 1.8.x.
Add RTD badge; switch from pypip.in to badge.fury.io.
We'll just support the Python versions that exist.
Update AUTHORS, changelog, and docs for PostGIS backend.
